As discussed, I am sharing your profile for Opus Technologies in Pune.

Company Name- Opus Technologies
Job Title: DevOps Site Reliability Engineer (AWS)/ FTE(Permanent)
Location – Pune(Hybrid)
Exp – 10+ yrs. 

Summary:
We are seeking a highly motivated and experienced DevOps Site Reliability Engineer with strong AWS cloud expertise to join our growing team. The ideal candidate will be responsible for designing, implementing, and maintaining our AWS infrastructure and CI/CD pipelines,
driving automation, and ensuring the reliability, scalability, and security of our applications. This role requires a strong understanding of DevOps principles, AWS services, and a passion for building robust and efficient systems. 
Key Responsibilities:
 Cloud Infrastructure Management:
 Design, provision, and manage AWS infrastructure using Infrastructure as Code (IaC) principles (e.g.,   CloudFormation, Terraform).
 CI/CD Pipeline Implementation:
 Develop and maintain automated CI/CD pipelines for application deployments using tools like 
 Jenkins, AWS Code Pipeline, or similar.
 Automation and Scripting:
 Automate infrastructure provisioning, application deployments, and other operational tasks using   scripting languages (e.g., Python, Shell) and configuration management tools (e.g., Ansible, Chef).
 Monitoring and Alerting:
 Implement and manage monitoring solutions (e.g., CloudWatch, Prometheus) to track system performance, identify potential issues, and ensure application availability.
 Security and Compliance:
 Implement and maintain security best practices within the AWS environment, ensuring compliance   with relevant regulations and standards.
 Troubleshooting and Problem Solving:
 Troubleshoot production issues, identify root causes, and implement corrective actions to minimize   downtime and ensure service availability.


 Qualifications:
Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or related field.
Proven experience (6+ years) in DevOps Site Reliability engineering roles with a focus on AWS cloud.
Strong understanding of AWS services, including EC2, S3, RDS, VPC, IAM, Lambda, CloudFormation, CloudWatch, etc.
Experience with CI/CD pipelines and tools (e.g., Jenkins, AWS CodePipeline).
Proficiency in scripting languages (e.g., Python, Shell) and configuration management tools (e.g., Ansible, Chef).
Experience with containerization technologies (e.g., Docker, Kubernetes), Linux is a plus.
Strong problem-solving and troubleshooting skills.
Excellent communication and collaboration skills.
AWS Certified DevOps Engineer (Professional) or similar certification is a plus. 
